replies.body:
@StealWolverine,

To answer your question, anything over your monitor's refresh rate is a waste. Most monitors run at 60Hz, which basically means it can refresh a maximum of 60 times a second. This equates to 60FPS - so a solid 60FPS would be the ideal scenario.

If you have less than 60FPS, you get lag. If you have more than 60FPS, you get syncing issues - screen tearing and the like. Everything over that 60 is wasted :-)
